  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">EJCW is the lead organization in the implementation of AB 685, the human right to water act of California of 2012. EJCW is a coalition of affected community groups throughout the state of California including tribes. The grant supports two important streams of the implementation of the Act: a) regional water board policy development following AB 685; and b) California State Water Board administrative action to require AB 685 implementation on the CA Water Bond funded &quot;Delta&quot; re development plan. The grant also support EJCW national advocacy on the human rights to water and sanitation, including engaging international mechanisms and federal agencies. The grant supports general staffing for EJCW to carry out these activities.</narrative>
  </description>
